BCD(6)

NNAAMMEE
     bbccdd, pppptt, mmoorrssee â€” reformat input
     as punch cards, paper tape or morse code

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     bbccdd [_s_t_r_i_n_g _._._.]  pppptt
     [--dd|_s_t_r_i_n_g _._._.]  mmoorrssee
     [--ddss _s_t_r_i_n_g _._._.]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     The bbccdd, pppptt and mmoorrssee commands
     read the given input and reformat it in the form of
     punched cards, paper tape or morse code respectively.
     Acceptable input are command line arguments or the
     standard input.

     Available option:

     --ss    The --ss option for morse produces dots and
     dashes rather than words.

     --dd    Decode pppptt output, or mmoorrssee
     output consisting of dots and slashes
           (as generated by using the --ss option).

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
     _I_S_O _1_6_8_1_:_1_9_7_3_:
     _I_n_f_o_r_m_a_t_i_o_n
     _p_r_o_c_e_s_s_i_n_g_-_-_U_n_p_u_n_c_h_e_d
     _p_a_p_e_r
     _c_a_r_d_s_-_-_S_p_e_c_i_f_i_c_a_t_i_o_n.

     _I_S_O _1_6_8_2_:_1_9_7_3_:
